# ADR Conventions

- ADR files live in `docs/adr/` and are indexed in `docs/adr/README.md`.
- Keep the numbering scheme already used in this repository: `ADR-XXX-kebab-title.md`.
- When creating a new ADR, increment from the highest existing number and update the README index in the same change.
- Write ADR prose in French.

## Required Sections

- `# ADR-XXX: Title`
- `## Status`
- `## Date`
- `## Context`
- `## Decision`
- `## Consequences`
- `## Alternatives`
- `## References` (optional)

## Scope

- Use ADRs for repository-wide architectural, tooling, or cross-cutting technical decisions.
- Do not use ADRs for local implementation notes or open exploration; use `docs/prospective/` for exploratory documents.
